  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (44f26a8 2022-05-25T00:10:19.746458Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\ninit, install\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Intel)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n~`forge init` immediately fails because it's not in a git repo~. The new root directory is still created but there's an error message which can be misleading. I believe it's because of the status check in #1696 \r\n\r\n```\r\n‚ùØ forge init hello_world\r\nInitializing /Users/bh/Projects/hello_world...\r\nInstalling forge-std in \"/Users/bh/Projects/hello_world/lib/forge-std\" (url: Some(\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std\"), tag: None)\r\nError:\r\n   0: fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/cmd/forge/install.rs:184\r\n```",
